Pollution Rule Delayed Amid Cost Complaints
The Obama administration suspended a new regulation aimed at cutting pollution from boilers at oil refineries, chemical plants and other factories, amid complaints by a range of industries over the potential cost.
Monday's announcement by the Environmental Protection Agency marks at least a temporary victory for industry and congressional critics of the administration's regulatory policies. The boiler rule is the latest in a series of EPA regulations the administration has scaled back or delayed amid criticism that jobs would...